      "writtenOn": "2020-10-23T22:01:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Fine, added. But it seems redundant (it just moves SHA256 calculation from the client to the server). My motivation for not adding it was relative obscurity of DetachTags. It is not exposed via \"cipd\" CLI interface and using is discouraged. So convenience of using it is supposedly not a problem.\n\nA pro of supporting raw key-value here is that DetachMetadataRequest now looks similar to DetachTagsRequest, which is nice.",
